originalText.text: I almost walked out of this office.  Although the interior is beautiful, wheelchair accessible and the people were super nice, they kept me waiting with no explanation.  And the first person I saw  - Ada?-wanted me to have ANOTHER  full set of x-rays even though I had just had a full set at my referring dentist's office.  She just looked heavenward when I said I was thinking of leaving and politely shook her head 'no'.  You need to see Dr. Genov, she said, politely.  He is the best dentist.  Polite, quiet but firm.  And he WAS! He gave me a discount on my x-rays, even though even I could see the ones his office took were much better, more clear than my own dentists x-rays.  And then he gave me the most painless shot to the jaw I've ever had, and started the root canal 15 minutes later. I did not feel ANY pain, even though I anticipated I would.  He stopped mid procedure and said I am not finishing this job, because the whole tooth is crack and needs to be pulled.  The charged me less than 1/3 of their initial predicted cost. Cannot express how happy I was, and glad that Ada(?) made me stay.

originalText.text: Dr. Genov is a great dentist. Very caring, professional and friendly. He’s the go-to dentist if you need a root canal. I highly recommend him. Thank you, Dr. Genov.

originalText.text: Dr. Genov is a brilliant Endodontics Practitioner!  I recently went to him for my root canal in horrible pain and he healed me immediately.  He walked me through the procedure and answered all of my questions.  He is also very caring.  He is the best.  Very happy and highly recommend.
